  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The efficacy of the cryoablation procedure at 12 months, defined as the absence of recurrences of atrial fibrillation.</measure>
    <time_frame>12 months</time_frame>
    <description>Recurrence of AF will be defined as a clinically diagnosed episode of AF and accordingly documented (on ECG, Holter monitor with a duration of at least 30 seconds or implantable devices or event recording systems).</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>The acute efficacy of the procedure:</measure>
    <time_frame>24-48h</time_frame>
    <description>complete isolation of the pulmonary veins demonstrated by the successful electrical disconnection of the pulmonary veins in the cryoablation procedure.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
